  "prompt": "How do you know I'd your pregnant?",
  "response": "You can suspect you might be pregnant based on several signs and symptoms, including:\n\n1. **Missed Period**: One of the most common early signs of pregnancy is a missed menstrual period.\n\n2. **Pregnancy Tests**: Over-the-counter home pregnancy tests can detect the hormone hCG (human chorionic gonadotropin) in your urine, which is produced after a fertilized egg attaches to the uterus.\n\n3. **Symptoms**: Other early symptoms may include:\n   - Nausea or vomiting (often referred to as morning sickness)\n   - Tender or swollen breasts\n   - Increased urination\n   - Fatigue\n   - Mood swings\n   - Light spotting or cramping (known as implantation bleeding)\n\n4. **Changes in Appetite**: Some women experience cravings or aversions to certain foods.\n\n5. **Basal Body Temperature**: If you have been tracking your basal body temperature, a sustained high temperature post-ovulation may indicate pregnancy.\n\nIf you suspect you might be pregnant, consider taking a test or consulting a healthcare provider for confirmation and advice.",
